From ad6efccc57e0cfa38e1f795b74c96e2ee0884e9b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mitch Hunt <mitch.w.hunt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 11:20:40 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] Show sharp vs public money split on every potential bet

Adds a sharp-vs-public lean estimate to each edge opportunity, computed
from data already fetched (no extra API credits):

- odds-math: SHARP_BOOK_KEYS (pinnacle, lowvig, betonlineag) + isSharpBook
- ev/props scanners: devigged consensus probability averaged separately
  across sharp books (sharpProb) and public books (publicProb), null when
  no book in that group quotes the outcome
- openapi spec + regenerated orval/zod clients
- web LiveEdges: Sharp / Public column in game-lines and props tables,
  plus the log-bet dialog card
- mobile: split shown on edge rows and the log sheet card
- tests locking in the split math and the null case

Note: The Odds API publishes no real bet/handle splits, so this is a
price-based proxy for where sharp money leans, not actual money split.
